cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.AI. 

The paper focuses on improving face recognition performance using deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and proposes a framework called SeqFace that utilizes sequence data to train the CNNs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of label smoothing regularization (LSR) and a new proposed discriminative sequence agent (DSA) loss, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, suggesting that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of video data, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper's focus on improving discrimination power of deep face features suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
